functional interfaces are introduced in java 8 
A functional interface in Java is an interface that contains 
only a single abstract (unimplemented) method.

Functional Interface is also known as Single Abstract Method Interfaces or SAM Interfaces



ANY INTERFACE CAN BE CALLED AS FUNCTIONAL INTERFACE IN JAVA
WHERE IT IS HAS ONLY ONE METHOD. WITHOUT NO IMPLEMENTATION. 

example:

public interface MyFunctionalInterface {
    public void execute();  // DECLARATION, there is no definition of execute.
}